        One night while I was at home a storm began to fall, it was raining
        vertiginously and I could only hear the sound of water on the ceiling,
        however, in the darkness of my room, a small tinkling sound began to
        resound that left me unsettled; a drop of water falling periodically on
        the floor, a drop of water falling periodically on the ceiling, a drop
        of water falling periodically on the floor. on the floor. When I decided
        to stand up, I realized that this tiny leak had turned into a puddle and
        with resignation, I proceeded to mop the floor and place a bucket at two
        o'clock in the morning. That same week, one afternoon, again in my room,
        I could hear what seemed to be the preamble of another downpour; the
        wind, puffing through the cracks of the windows, and the light dimming
        little by little. Again, without warning, like the desperate leak the
        other night, a strange sound forced me to look up at the roof. I seemed
        to hear earth falling from the sky. Well, such a particular sound
        deserved concentration to know its origin; and so, after a few minutes I
        found out, frightened, that when the wind blew, dust fell from the roof.
        Now I understood the reason for the dirt in my room. After this I
        concluded that I had to fix the roof of my house.
    </p>

